Title : 1981 Falkland Islands general election
Text : {{Politics of the Falkland Islands}}
The '''Falkland Islands general election of 1981''' was held on Thursday 1 October 1981 to elect members to the [[Legislative Council of the Falkland Islands|Legislative Council]]. Six Councillors were elected through [[universal suffrage]], one from each constituency ([[Camp (constituency)|Camp]], [[East Falkland (constituency)|East Falkland]], [[East Stanley (constituency)|East Stanley]], [[West Falkland (constituency)|West Falkland]], [[West Stanley (constituency)|West Stanley]] and [[Stanley (constituency)|Stanley]]).

==Results==
Candidates in '''bold''' were elected.  Candidates in ''italic'' were incumbents.

